betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Dragon was banished from the face of the Earth, but she didn't go without leaving her mark on the world.

The skies themselves are cursed; diseased with a slow growth of skin that, given time, will cover the Earth in utter darkness.

The only way to break the curse is to travel to the End and kill the Dragon, retrieve her egg, and place it on Earth. But the way to the End is locked, and the keys are guarded by her minions, and scattered... across the Multiverse.

You'll need a number of materials to complete your quest... time to start mining.

This is by no means an exhaustive list of the materials you'll need... just the basics.

You'll need a way to turn metals (and other materials) into dust. Not only are they required for crafting, but they can also double your ore output.

Some early options are:
 * Crusher (Actually Additions)
 * Manufactory (Nuclearcraft)

Some later options you can use as you unlock mods:
 * Pulverizer (Thermal Expansion)
 * Enrichment chamber and Crusher (Mekanism)
 * Sag Mill (Ender IO)
 * Quartz Grindstone (Applied Energistics) -- has to be hand-cranked, but the only option that doesn't require power

Not all machines are capable of crushing all items... use JEI to see what does what!

You'll need to smelt those metal ores into ingots to make use of them. You could just dump them in a furnace... but eventually you'll want something that will increase your ore output. One option is the various crushing machines (see the Don't Breathe This! quest). Another is the Tinker's Construct smeltery. (See the book Materials and You)
The Diamond Key is hidden in the overworld, guarded by the Diamond Husk. You must seek his tower, the Broken Sphere, and take the key from him.

Steel is one of the most commonly used alloys, and you'll need to learn how to make some.

Some early options:
 * Immersive Engineering Blast Furnace (See the Engineer's Manual for details)
 * Iron and coal in the Alloy Furnace

Some later options:
 * Iron and pulverized coal or charcoal in an Induction Smelter
 * Iron and either coal or charcoal in the Metallurgic Infuser

Besides steel, there are many other alloys you'll need, which are made from a combination of metals (and sometimes other materials).

Early options:
* Alloy Furnace from NuclearCraft
* Alloy Kiln from Immersive Engineering (see Engineer's Manual)
* Smeltery from Tinker's Construct (see Materials and You)
* Simpler alloys can be made by mixing the dusts together in the appropriate ratio in a crafting bench

Later options:
* Alloy Smelter from EnderIO
* Induction Smelter from Thermal Expansion
* Metallurgic Infuser from Mekanism

As always, not every machine can make every alloy, so check JEI to see what your options are.

You'll need a way to generate RF power to run most of the machines you'll need.

Just a few options are ...
* Dynamos from Thermal Expansion
* Furnace or Survivalist generators from Extra Utilities 2
* Coal (and later, canola oil) generator from Actually Additions
* Wind (or solar, but that's more complicated) generator from Mekanism
* Stirling generator from EnderIO
* Decay generator from NuclearCraft (craft one and plonk down some Uranium or Thorium blocks next to it)

Some of these options may require unlocking their associated mods first.

To get into the Nether, you'll first need to get some Obsidian and a Flint and Steel. The simplest way to get Obsidian is to pour water onto lava and bash it out with a diamond (or better) pick, but if you're willing to dig into JEI a little you might find some machines to make it for you instead.

Plonk down 4 soul sand in a T shape, then plonk 3 wither skeleton skulls on top.

Then stand back.

And arm yourself to the teeth first.

When you're done, take his star and break it open to retrieve the key inside.
The key ingredient for Actually Additions machines. You can find it in the Nether.

Zaps stuff into other stuff.

Handy tip: Right-click it with a redstone torch until it's in 'pulse' mode. Then place it on top of a block, put a wood pressure plate in front of it, and throw stuff onto the pressure plate to zap it.
Like the Thaumcraft infusion alter... but more technical.
Throw a diamond at the Atomic Reconstructor... then throw the result at the empowerer with the other bits.
Create a 2x2 pool of water, surround it with plants (flowers, grass, saplings, whatever), and throw in the empowered diamatine.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Why did it have to be snakes?
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Once in the Twilight Forest, look for the Naga in its stone arena, and kill it. Taking the Naga Scales will allow you to reach the Twilight Lich
Find the Twilight Lich atop his tower. Bat his projectiles back at him until his shields are gone, then finish him off. Picking up his sceptre will allow access to the swamp maze.
Find the Labyrinth within the Twilight Swamp. Traverse the maze and find the Minoshroom, and kill him. Eat one of the Meef Stroganoff to gain access to the Hydra.
The Ruby Key is guarded by the Hydra. Find him in his lair in the Fire Swamp. Kill him.
To summon the Wither, you'll need some soul sand and Wither skeleton skulls. You can usually find the latter in nether fortresses; a sword with a few levels of beheading are highly recommended.
The Engineer's Hammer: The key to building Immersive Engineering structures

Put down coke bricks in a 3x3x3 cube, then thwack the front side with the engineer's hammer.

Then shovel some coal or logs into it to start generating creosote oil.

Logs will turn into charcoal; coal will turn into coke, which is useful for making steel.
Get a bottle (or other fluid container) of creosote oil from the coke oven and surround it with 8 planks of wood. Any old wood.
The Engineer's Workbench. Useful for making a number of crafting components.

These will be necessary to make a circuit board... but they're also handy for making RF wiring. You can snip them from copper plates, or you can build the Metal Press (see the Engineer's Manual) if you're going to be making them regularly.

You'll need a way to make metal plates. You could just hammer some out with the engineer's hammer... but that's inefficient. You could build a Metal Press (see the Engineer's Manual), or a Compactor, or just smelt them in the Tinker's Smeltery.
You'll need vacuum tubes to make a circuitboard
You'll need to make a circuit board to build a Resonator, needed to open the portal to Atum
Build a Resonator, and throw the Tropics wand into it. Unlike most Resonator recipes, this needs no power.

To build the portal to Atum:

1. Place a 5x5 block of sandstone
2. Place a 1-block thick 'ring' of sandstone on top of it, and fill it with water
3. Place a 2-block tall pillar of sandstone at each corner
4. Finally, throw the scarab into the water.

Then... jump in!

The Amethyst key is held by the Pharaoh, in the realm of Atum.

Search the sands of Atum for a pyramid. Dig out the bottom of the 'stairs' until you find a doorway. Navigate the dungeon within until you find the sarcophagus.

Place four Royal Torches around the corners of the sarcophagus (or, if they're already there, relight them with a torch). Then, open the sarcophagus to bring the Pharaoh to life.

Once he's dead, you'll find the key within the sarcophagus
Next, you'll need to make a Morb. And a reusable one at that.

You'll need to make Slag, which can be done in two ways:

* Smelt some metal dusts in the Induction Smelter

* Make some steel in the IE Blast Furnace

You'll need a bit of melted ender pearls to make the hunting portal frame. There's several ways to make it, including the magma crucible, the Nuclearcraft melter, or even just the smeltery. Melt some, pour it in a tank, and scoop it up with a bucket.
You'll need Certus Quarts to unlock Thermal Expansion, RFTools, and Applied Energistics

Now take the morb and throw it at a zombie. Dunk it in some resonant ender, and pour it on 4 logs to make the frame for the hunting portal. Build it like a Nether portal, then right-click it with a sword to activate it.

(You need to sneak into it to pass through.)

You might want to fence it off... sometimes hostile mobs will wander through.
You can find Porphyry in both the Hunting Dimension and the Mining Dimension. It generates like andesite and similar minerals.

Signalum is an alloy made of Copper, Silver and Redstone in a 3:1:10 ratio. It has a few uses, one of which is making locks for securing machines.

There's a few ways to make it:

* Signalum Blend plus sand in the Induction Smelter. (You'll need to use the Magma Crucible to melt down the redstone to make the blend)

* Make Shibuichi alloy from Copper and Silver in the Alloy Furnace, then melt down some redstone in a Melter (or Magma Crucible) and pipe the whole lot into a Fluid Infuser

* Throw all three in the Alloy Smelter

* Throw all three into the Tinker's Smeltery
You'll need some grid power to run the resonator. There's several ways of generating it, but most of them require some solar power to get started.
The Tin Key is hidden in the everlasting darkness of the Hunting World, guarded by the Lost Hunter. Look for him atop the Horned Tower.

Search the world to find some mystical flowers.

Or brew up some Floral Fertilizer and grow your own.

The start of the Botania tech tree is the Petal Apothecary.

Consult the Lexica Botania to learn more.

A lot of Botania constructs require livingwood and livingrock... for which you'll need a Pure Daisy to create.

Throw some water into the apothecary, throw in four white petals, and finally throw in some seeds.
Not technically required. But it tells you how to do stuff.
Not strictly required. But tells you how to do stuff.

Not strictly required. But tells you how to do stuff.

(It will also pop up automatically when you start building AA machines)
Plonk some logs and/or stone down adjacent (including diagonally) to the Pure Daisy and wait a minute.
Basically, Botania's version of a wrench.
The Mana Spreader transports mana over short distances
The Mana Pool is used to store mana
One of the most basic mana-generating flowers, this generates mana by burning solid fuels
Some very common mana-infused resources
The next tier of technology requires Runes. And that requires a Runic Alter

A magical alloy that needs a bunch of mana to create.

Create a checkerboard pattern out of livingrock and lapis blocks, plonk the agglomeration plate on top, then place a spark above it and a mana pool.

To create terrasteel, fill the mana pool at least half full, then drop a mana diamond, mana pearl, and manasteel on the plate and stand back.

The Elven Gateway will open a portal to Alfheim, allowing you to trade with the Elves for rare and valuable resources.

Read the Lexica Botania to learn how to build the structure.

The Silver Key is hidden in the sky realm of the Aether.

To reach it, you'll need to build a portal out of Glowstone Blocks (in the same shape as a Nether portal), and activate it by pouring water into it from a skyroot bucket.

You'll need to get skyroot. It can only found naturally in the Aether, but you can make it using the Conjuration Catalyst. Throw an oak sapling and a piece of dirt into a catalyst-equipped mana pool, then plant the resulting sapling on the resulting dirt.

The Silver Key is held by the Queen Valkyrie in her temple in the sky. Kill ten of her minions, then talk to her.

(Note that the key she drops §oisn't§o§r the silver key for the quest. You'll find that in her treasure chest, which you §owill§r need her key to open.)
Go find a gecko and cage him up. For ... alchemical purposes.

The good news: You don't have go hunting all over the countryside for meteorites anymore. You just need to find one. You can duplicate whatever press(es) you find and convert them into the others using sky stone dust.
You'll need Certus Quartz to get started with AE2. You can find it in the Twilight Forest. Charged Certus doesn't generate naturally, but can be created using Thermal Foundation's Energetic Infuser
Throw some charged certus, nether quartz, and redstone into the nearest pond and wait a moment.

You'll need these to make ME circuits. Unlike most ME machines, these run on RF power.

You can also make advanced inscribers. Those do run on AE power, so you'll need to power it from an energy acceptor

You'll need one of these to grow pure crystals. It runs on AE power, so you'll need an energy acceptor to run it from RF power.

You can also use it to grow fluix crystals, instead of tossing the ingredients into water.

You can turn one certus quartz into two pure certus crystals by grinding it into dust, mixing it with sand, then putting it in the growth chamber. The pure versions can be used almost anywhere the regular ones can (for half the cost), and are also required for calculation processors.

You can do the same with nether quartz and fluix crystals.
You'll need lots of these for various ME devices

You'll need silicon to make energistics circuitry. There's a few ways to do it.

* Smelt up some ground certus or nether quartz

* Sand in the Mekanism crusher

* Clay or sand in the SAG mill. (Sand only has a 50% chance to generate silicon)
Used to put ME storage units... but you'll also need them for Spatial IO

You'll need dimensional shards to build the portal to the mining world... and they can only be found within artificial dimensions.

First, you need a blank dimension tab, and a dimension enscriber to write to it.

You can just shovel the tab into the enscriber and create a random dimension, or build dimlets in a dimlet workbench, using bits of dimlets you've looted.
Not needed for your quest... but damn handy.
Used to move stuff into or out of storage units en masse... and also needed for Spatial IO
With the Spatio IO system, you can suqeeze a bunch of stuff in the world into a digital storage unit.
You'll need an ME controller in order to connect more than 8 devices in an ME network

The Gold Key is held by a Blaze hidden away in ME spatial storage.

You'll need a 4x4x4 spacial chamber. Use the pylons to build a 5x5x5 wireframe, minus the corners. Then connect them to an ME network. Each strip of pylons requires a channel (12 in total) so you'll need an ME controller to connect them all.

Once you've built the chamber, attach the spatial IO port to the network, place the storage unit into the left side of it, and give it a redstone pulse.

The spatial storage unit holding the gold key is hidden away in Ender Space. You'll need to build an ender chest (from Ender Storage) and key it to the following colors: Red, Orange, Yellow. (Get some dyes of that color, then click the key pieces at the top of the chest.)

The storage cell will regenerate one minute after being taken out of the chest, so you can reload it if you screw up and lose the key, or are playing multiplayer.
Not strictly required. But quite informative.
Once you have a dimension tab, you'll need to put it into the world builder, and wait for it to create the world.

You'll need a Matter Transmitter to teleport into your brand new dimension, and a Dialing Device to program it.

You'll also need a way to get back. One way is to place a receiver in your base, take another transmitter and dialer with you, and something to power it all up wtih. But there's other options...
Dimensional shards can be found in ore form, randomly strewn throughout RFtools dimensions.
Once you have dimensional shards, you can now create the portal to the mining world.
The Sapphire Key is hidden in an underground laboratory hidden in the mining world. Only a small elevator shaft can be seen above the ground...
You'll need Grains of Infinity to get unlock Ender IO. Dig down to the bottom of the Deep Dark, clear out a space, and set a bunch of bedrock on fire
You'll need to make quite a few of these.
You'll need these alloys for lots of EnderIO stuff
These will improve the performance of your machines. They're also necessary for some of the advanced machihnes
The base of almost every EnderIO machine

A block of blast-resistant glass.

Can also generally be used in recipes that call for hardened glass.
You'll probably want to get a sword with Beheading on it for this one.

betterquesting:10.name:8: What does SAG stand for anyway?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You'll need these machines to make the industrial dyes required for later items.

They can also be used for grinding stuff and making alloys.
At what point does this cease being science and become eldritch magics?

The Lead Key is guarded by the Tarantula Brood Mother. Look for her nest in her giant tree.

Once she's dead, take her egg and break it open to retrieve the key within.
Use the heads of your fallen enemies ... as circuitry?
Use the souls of your fallen enemies ... in machinery?
Make a soul vial and trap an enderman in it. Then infuse it into a crystal.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Use Your Head... actually use someone else's
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Turns out, enderman heads make for good control circuits

betterquesting:10.name:8: There is such a thing as a tesseract.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Teleport things across dimensions

betterquesting:10.name:8: An Earthen Staff has a knob on the end
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Throw an obsidian, a diamond, and an emerald onto the offering table and wait a moment

The Lead Key is hidden away in the Erebus... an underground world of giant arthropods.

Build a portal frame (similar to a Nether portal) out of stone bricks, fill it with leaves, plonk the keystone in front of it and place the staff on it.

Very important: There will be a return portal built on the other side when you enter the Erebus... but it will be deactivated. You'll need to build a second staff to return... or bring some other manner of teleportation with you.
These occasionally drop from redstone ore... but there's ways of crafting them as well.
Like a crafting table... but requires Grid Power. (Read the EU2 manual to learn how to generate it)
Not strictly required... unless you acutally need to learn how to use all this stuff.
You'll need a casting gauntlet to activate arcane infusions. Check out the 'auromancy' knowledge tree in the Thaumonomicon
Build a rocket (See the JPL quest for details), and fly it to the moon.

The Copper Key is hidden in the Deep Dark... an underground realm where the darkness is alive. And angry.

To reach it, first you must dig deep into the sands of Atum until you find Khnumite. Dig some up, create a face out of it using a diamond, then place it into the resonator
A common swamp tree, used for many things

The Copper Key is guarded by a giant spider in a glass dome in the Deep Dark.

She moves fast. You might want to be ready for that.
Find a sap tree and chop it down. The sap can ward off the Decay
Transfer items (or fluids, or energy) without pipes!
This is ... pretty much the Betweenland's equivalent of iron.
Once you have some syrmorite, make some shears, grab some moss and make a bed. Else you might respawn in a highly hostile environment
Just a wad of filth. But useful for summoning eldritch horrors.
You'll need this stuff to make torches that work in the Betweenlands
Murder some Peat Mummies in marshes to get this
Find some Sludge Plains and murder some Tar Beasts.
...the heart beats again!
Kill these undead beings and tear the heart out of ... what's left of their chest
A rare crystal, used as a power source. You can find them deep in the caves. Look for stalagmites with glowing white stripes at the base.

Find a druid altar in a swamp and murder some druids until you get the four pieces of the swamp talisman -- one of them inactive.

Tune an entangloporter into the 'Swamp Magic' frequency. Pipe the inactive piece into it, wait a moment, then pipe out the final, activated piece of the talisman.

Assemble the talisman at the altar near the druid hangout, then use it on a sapling to make a portal to the Betweenlands.

The Betweenlands is a swampy world. Be aware that many overworld things won't work in the moist environment, including food, torches, and firestarters, and overworld weapons lose their efficiency as well.
These grow like sugar cane in watery, swampy biomes
Kill some lurkers, kick over some hollow logs, and make a book to record your alchemical discoveries in.

Grind up various bits of plant and animal and feed the result to your gecko.

For science.

Or maybe alchemy.

The next tier of Astral crafting. Plonk a crafting table down in a mystical shrine and use it to craft one.

You'll need starlight for this and many Astral devices. If a device isn't receiving enough starlight, you can try moving it to a different place in the world, or higher in altitude.

You'll need an unobstructed view of the sky, which can be tricky when the sky is covered by disease. But there are other dimensions with clear night skies...

Used extensively for aerospace purposes.

Look for Rutile Ore. It can't be smelted in normal furnaces. You could build the Electric Arc Furnace to smelt it, or just use one of several ore-grinding machines and smelt the dust.

This will show you how to build the various multiblock machines.

Shift-right click to select the machine you want to build. Click and drag the background to scroll around the list of machines.

Right-click the ground where you want to build. Shift-mousewheel to cycle between vertical layers.
You could build the Electric Arc Smelter to make this. But the NuclearCraft manufactory is probably easier.
Build a Crystallizer and put some silicon in it to make a boule
Build a cutting machine and use that to cut the boule into wafers
Build a Precision Assembler and add some gold and redstone to the wafer to make circuitry
Throw the circuit plate back into the cutting machine to make circuits

Everything needed to build a rocket.

To build the launch pad, place down a square launch pad made out of launch pad blocks, place a vertical stack of structure towers on the outside edge (with one touching the side of the pad), and then put the assembling machine on the outside edge, one block above the launch pad.

The rocket itself is a more-or-less freeform multiblock. As long as you have enough fuel and engines, you can make it any size and shape you want. You'll also need a seat to ride it, and a guidance computer to control where it goes.
You'll need a spacesuit to venture into places without a breathable atmosphere
Hold the wand in your hand and walk around at night until you see sparkles in the ground. Then dig.

You'll need to build an Electrolyzer (a multiblock structure) in order to generate oxygen for your space suit. Pipe plain old water into it to separate it into hydrogen (which you'll need for fuel) and oxygen.

You'll also need at least one pressure tank (of any tier), a suit workbench to install it into your chestpiece, and a gas charge pad to fill it.

(As with the other machines, the Electrolyzer and the Rolling Machine are multiblock structures. Use the Holo-Projector to see how to build them)
The key to teleportation technology
These mystical gems can be found among the sand in bodies of water
Search the world for a starlight shrine made of marble. Dig into it to find a mystic crystal, and some loot.
The 'wrench' of Astral Sorcery -- You'll need the Arcane Crafting Table to create it
Marble comes in a few different forms. There's crafting recipes to make the different forms out of plain marble... or you could just use a chisel.

Make a light well and stick some aquamarine in it, and light itself will condense into a liquid.

Yeah. I don't know how that works either.
An essential element of all Mekanism machines
Makes a number of essential components for Mekansim machines
Toss a piece of redstone and iron into the infuser

Toss a piece of diamond and an enriched alloy into the infuser.

Better yet, make an enrichment chamber, toss a diamond in it, and put the resulting compressed diamond into the infuser with §oeight§r enriched alloys.
Crush some obsidian, and put the dust into the infuser with a diamond. (Or, again, make compressed diamond in the enrichment chamber and make eight times as much with a single diamond)
Put some refined obsidian dust (you can compress this in the enrichment chamber too!) and reinforced alloy into the infuser
Redstone and osmium in the infuser
Regular control circuits upgraded with advanced alloys
Make an osmium compressor, then throw in some refined obsidian and osmium

The third tier of Astral crafting.

(The ritual actually upgrades the Luminous crafting table in place. Just pick it up to complete the quest.)
Not strictly necessary... if you already know how it all works.
Link Astral devices and resources to each other
Dig out a shrine so the crystal has a view of the sky. Then stick some iron ore in it and link it to the collector crystal

The next tier of Astral crafting, and the one you need to make the key to the End.

(As before, you need to pick up the altar to get quest credit)

Finally, you have everything you need to access the End.

Craft the End Key from all the other keys. Find a stronghold, open the portal, and right-click it with the key to unlock it.

Note that the key only unlocks the portal for §oyou§r. If you're playing multiplayer, you can duplicate the initial key by crafting it with an ender eye.
Find her. Kill her. Place her egg in the world to end the plague.

Use this to harvest up some plant products, put them into the mortar and pestle, punch it to ground them up, then feed them to your caged gecko.

(Try grinding up animal products too)
A valuable gem found deep underground
A fiery metal found in the Betweenlands caverns
A cauldron to boil magical elements out of items
Find a rubber tree, and right-click it with a syrmorite bucket. Then smelt it.
Look for these in the stumps of large weedwood trees
Used for Betweenlands alchemy
Purify alchemical infusions

Once you determine what substance contains Armaniis, put it in the infuser with some swamp water, light a fire under it, and right-click it to stir it until it changes color. Then shift-right-click with a weedwood bucket, and pour the result into the alembic. When it's done, right-click with aspect vials until it's empty.

(You can shift-right click a vial onto the ground and pour more of the same aspect into it to consolidate. Also, you don't need the exact amount, you just need one unit.)

To make rocket fuel, pipe the hydrogen and oxygen from the electrolyzer into a chemical reactor. You can store it in tanks and load them into your rocket using a fueling station. Use the linker to connect the fueling station to the rocket.

(The chemical reactor is, once again, a multiblock.)
The Emerald Key is held by the Dreadful Peat Mummy. Use the resources and knowledge you've gathered, and summon it by creating Mummy Bait and throwing it down in a Sludge Plains biome,

To travel out of the solar system, you'll need to build a starship.

First, you need to place a space station in orbit. To do that, build a station builder structure in the same fashion as building a rocket launch pad, except place down a space station assembler instead of a rocket assembler. (You can also reuse your rocket launch pad and just place the station assembler next to the rocket assembler.)

Then you can build the space station in pretty much any size and shape you want, as long as it fits on the pad. Once you're ready to launch it, place an empty satellite bay and an unprogrammed satellite id chip into the satellite builder and build it.

Then, build a rocket as before, except this time add a satellite bay to it. Place the satellite from the builder into the satellite bay, and the ID chip into the guidance computer. Fuel the rocket, jump on, and launch, and you'll land on your new satellite!

Next, you'll need to install a warp core into your space station. This is another multiblock structure, so break out your holo-projector.

You'll then need to place down a warp controller somewhere on your ship. This one is just a single block.

Once you've warped to a destination, you can use the rocket you launched the station with to shuttle back and forth to the planet.
You'll need dilithium to fuel the warp drive. You'll find it on Earth's Moon. Find some ore, grind it up, and put it into the crystallizer to make crystals.
The Quicksilver key is held by a Vindicator on Alpha Centauri IIIa. Warp there, find him in his toroid tower, and kill him.
Mine it in Extreme Hills biomes, or sell some crap to a villager
...buying money with money?
Reasonably abundant resources found in the Nether

Metals found fairly commonly in the Nether, they make good Tinker's tools.

You'll need an Obsidian pickaxe (made with the Tinkers crafting stations) to obtain them.
Useful for building and fueling nuclear reactors
...whose?
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.

You'll need some Vis Crystals in order to study thaumaturgical magic.

You can make them by zapping some crystals in the Atomic Reconstructor, breaking them down, then throwing them in a mana pool. You can also find them in deposits on the surface of the Aether. 

Grab a few different flavors ... then follow your instincts

§o§o§rYou really §odo§r need this one to progress.

To progress in Thaumcraft, you have to study various lines of research in the Thaumononicon. Many lines of research require the appropriate knowledge in a given field; these requirements will be shown at the bottom of the first page of that section.

To gain knowledge, scan items with the thaumometer, or do research at the research table.

You'll need these to perform research. Read about them in the thaumonomicon.

(You need to pick the table up to get the reward)

betterquesting:10.name:8: Based on the play by Arthur Miller
betterquesting:10.desc:8: A crucial step on the road to Alchemy
Boil items down into their magical components
Unlike money, magic§  apparently §odoes§r grow on trees.
Mix liquid essentia with stuff to make new stuff

You will need some materials to reconstitute the Air key.

First, an egg from a Moa, any color. Find some moas and wait until they lay one.

Then, find a Golden Oak tree, cut it down, and take a sapling.

Finally, dig down into the islands and look for some Gravitite.
You'll need to enchant the gravitite ore in order to use it. Find some zanite, build an enchanter, and put the gravitite into it with some ambrosium.

The Air key -- or the core of it -- is found in the Aether, held by the Slider. To find it, search the Aether for a stone opening in the ground. Go in, kill the Slider, and then search for his treasure chest.

Bring a pickaxe that does some damage; you'll need it to fight the Slider

The Infusion Alter is required to reconstitute the air key. Place the core on the central pedestal, place the egg, sapling, and gravitite onto the outer pedestals, and supply a jar with 10 units of Aer essense, and begin the infusion.

You might want to make some candles and surround the altar with them, to stabilize it. Make sure to make them symmetrical around the center of the alter, else it will just make matters worse.
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.
Sometimes you just need the most basic materials.
Kill animals for organic resources
Kill monsters for organic resources
Kill an enderman for its pearls
Kill some blazes for their rods
Kill some ghasts for their tears
Surely this is good for §osomething
Thigh bone connected to the hip bone
Creeper droppings
Find a bit of animal, vegetable, and mineral from the Erebus to reconstitute the Earth key

The Earth Key Core is held by the Antlion Overlord. Search the Erebus for his pyramid and solve the puzzles within to reach him.

Once he's dead, break open his egg to reveal the fragment within.
To reconstitute the Earth key, place the core and the materials on the Botania Infusion Alter and give it some mana. When it's ready, finish it off with a piece of livingrock
You'll need the sapling from a Spirit tree. Look for one in the Swamplands, then stab it in the face. Literally.
Find some bamboo, make some mugs, then make a drink mixer

Find some coconut and pineapple, cut them into chunks, then place both of them in the drink mixer, and then a bamboo mug.

(Right click the §obase§r of the mixer to add items)

The water key core is held by the Primordial Malevolence. Look for it in the Wight Tower in the marshes of the Betweenlands.

To kill it, you'll need to fling its own projectiles back into it using a sword, then attack while its shield segments are down.
You'll need to use the Empowerer to reconstitute the water key. Place a bucket of water on the empowerer, then place the core, the sapling, some valonite, and a wight heart on the display stands.

You'll need an arc furnace for the next step... and for that you'll need electrodes.

To start with, you'll need some coke dust. And for that, you'll need a crusher. Read the engineer's manual (and maybe build a projector) to learn how to build one
Next, you'll need an industrial squeezer to extract graphite from the coke dust. Once again, read the manual and use the projector
Smelt the graphite dust, and use the workbench to make electrodes out of it.
The Fire Key Core is held by a ghast in the Nether. Look for him in a fortress build in his likeness
You'll need a bit of glowstone, nether wart, and a ghast tear.
To reconstitute the key, you'll need to build an arc smelter. Then, put the core into furnace, along with the wart, tear, and glowstone. Then give it §olots§r of power.

Find some Chunks O' Head.

There are three ways to get them:

1. Find and murder an Easter Island Head mob. You'll need a pickaxe to kill it.

2. Find an Easter Island Head statue and mine the blocks it's made of. Careful of the lava inside.

3. Find a volcano, which is also made of chunk. Obviously the same caveat about lava applies.
